race.comment: FUN LOVIN CRIMINAL (2) hasn't made an impression lately despite market confidence. Last start could only manage sixth over 1609m at Mountaineer Park (Dirt). Can improve sharply. SWIFT TAP (4) is yet to find the winners' list this time in work but has six placings from nine appearances this campaign, finishing 0.3 lengths away in second most recently over 1408m at this track. Ready to find winning form. SPINNING HEART (6) finished fourth two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1609m at Penn National, beaten 11 lengths after being prominent at the turn. Taking on a better field but he is good enough to figure in the finish. GOODAFTERNOONOSCAR (8) hasn't been able to break through for an extended period, the latest effort a fourth over 1609m at Mountaineer Park (Dirt). Taking on a better field but he is good enough to take this out. Something for the Multiples: ROL AGAIN DANCER (5)
